dismissalComment.html: Stirling goes back in the crease and looks to cut the ball. He gets the faintest of edges through to Shahzad behind the stumps. He throws the ball high in the air, think he is happy about that one!
McBrine is gone now too! Its outside off-stump and McBrine comes down the pitch, it spins past the bat and Shahzad whips off the bails. Ireland in deep trouble now.

Wilson goes down the pitch and misses the ball. Shahzad takes off the bails and then does a little dance behind the stumps. Wilson just stands there and stares at him. That's not going to help the tension here.

dismissalText.commentary: Ed Joyce run out (Yamin Ahmadzai) 12 (21b 2x4 0x6) SR: 57.14

dismissalComment.html: well whats happening here. Joyce hits the ball to the extra cover boundary. The fielders chase the ball back and get it back in. Joyce thought that it had gone for the boundary and stopped running before the throw came back in.

dismissalText.commentary: William Porterfield run out (Samiullah Shinwari) 16 (27b 2x4 0x6) SR: 59.25

dismissalComment.html: Terry has run the Irish captain out! Terry hits the ball to the left of mid-wicket. Porterfield is watching the ball, Terry meets him at the non-strikers end and Porterfield charges down the other end. The dive can't save him.

dismissalText.commentary: Peter Chase c Mohammad Nabi b Dawlat Zadran 0 (7b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0

headshotImage.caption: Rashid Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Rashid Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c Mohammad Nabi b Dawlat Zadran
dismissalText.commentary: Peter Chase c Mohammad Nabi b Dawlat Zadran 0 (7b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0

commentTextItems.html: that's it, its all over. Chase pulls the ball into the legside and Nabi takes a simple catch to finish the match.

commentPostTextItems.html: So Afghanistan win today's game by 79 runs. Who would have thought that would have been the case when they were struglling on 109 for 6?
With only 2 batsmen who managed to get into the thirties, Ireland were never really in the chase. The two run outs at the top didn't help, yet whilst the Afghan's tail wagged, Ireland's didnt.
Rashid Arman was the pick of the Afghan's bowlers again, finishing off with 4 wickets.
Once again the inexperience of the Ireland lower order showed. Once O'Brien and Stirling was out it was a steady stream of Irish batsmen heading to the wicket and coming back again.
Its a shame that the game might be overshadowed by the fall of Joyce's wicket. I'm sure that we will be hearing more about it over the next couple of days.
So Afghanistan take a 2-1 lead in the series with only one game remaining, being played on Tuesday here in Stormont.
Will Afganistan put in another dominate performance, or will Ireland fight back again and level the series. It will not be dull I can promise you that.
So please join me on Tuesday to find out.
Until then, thanks for following my commentary today. This is Justin Smyth saying goodnight from Stormont.

dismissalText.commentary: Asghar Afghan c Joyce b McBrine 0 (4b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: what a catch from Joyce. Stanikzai smashes the ball in the air towards the square leg boundary, Joyce leaps up and takes a two handed catch just inside the rope. Stanikzai is out for a duck.

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Nabi c Chase b Murtagh 50 (67b 5x4 1x6) SR: 74.62

dismissalComment.html: Nabi is gone, what has he done? He gets set early to flick the ball round the corner. He doesn't catch it well and Chase uses all of his 6ft 4 frame to lean forward and catch the ball inches off the ground at short fine leg

dismissalText.commentary: William Porterfield run out (Samiullah Shinwari) 16 (27b 2x4 0x6) SR: 59.25

dismissalComment.html: Terry has run the Irish captain out! Terry hits the ball to the left of mid-wicket. Porterfield is watching the ball, Terry meets him at the non-strikers end and Porterfield charges down the other end. The dive can't save him.

dismissalText.commentary: Ed Joyce run out (Yamin Ahmadzai) 12 (21b 2x4 0x6) SR: 57.14

dismissalComment.html: well whats happening here. Joyce hits the ball to the extra cover boundary. The fielders chase the ball back and get it back in. Joyce thought that it had gone for the boundary and stopped running before the throw came back in.

milestones.description: Mirwais and Rashid Khan's 66-run partnership is AFG's highest for the 8th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 52 between Mohammad Nabi and Rashid Khan
Asghar Afghan has broken the record for most ducks (5) in ODIs for AFG, going past Dawlat Zadran's 4
Mohammad Nabi has become the top scorer for AFG in ODIs with 1578 runs, going past Shahzad's 1554
Dawlat Zadran has become the top wicket-taker for AFG in ODIs with 63 wickets, going past Mohammad Nabi's 62
Rahmat Shah has taken the most five-wicket hauls (1) in ODIs for AFG, going past Hamid Hassan's record
